      "message": "FWIW, I think if we were writing this directly in SSE this would be,\n\nSkM4\u0026 SkM4::setConcat(const SkM4\u0026 a, const SkM4\u0026 b) {\n    __m128 c0 \u003d _mm_loadu_ps(a.fMat +  0),\n           c1 \u003d _mm_loadu_ps(a.fMat +  4),\n           c2 \u003d _mm_loadu_ps(a.fMat +  8),\n           c3 \u003d _mm_loadu_ps(a.fMat + 12);\n\n    auto compute \u003d [\u0026](__m128 r) {\n        return _mm_add_ps(_mm_mul_ps(c0, _mm_shuffle_ps(r,r, 0x00)),\n               _mm_add_ps(_mm_mul_ps(c1, _mm_shuffle_ps(r,r, 0x55)),\n               _mm_add_ps(_mm_mul_ps(c2, _mm_shuffle_ps(r,r, 0xaa)),\n                          _mm_mul_ps(c3, _mm_shuffle_ps(r,r, 0xff)))));\n    };\n\n    __m128 m0 \u003d compute(_mm_loadu_ps(b.fMat +  0)),\n           m1 \u003d compute(_mm_loadu_ps(b.fMat +  4)),\n           m2 \u003d compute(_mm_loadu_ps(b.fMat +  8)),\n           m3 \u003d compute(_mm_loadu_ps(b.fMat + 12));\n\n    _mm_storeu_ps(fMat +  0, m0);\n    _mm_storeu_ps(fMat +  4, m1);\n    _mm_storeu_ps(fMat +  8, m2);\n    _mm_storeu_ps(fMat + 12, m3);\n    return *this;\n}\n\nDisassembling that gives me exactly what I would have expected.\nRunning m4_set_concat in nanobench looks unchanged.\n\nWith both approaches, it might be possible to reduce the latency by shortening the dependency tree in compute() be rearranging the math to something like (c0*r0 + c1*r1) + (c2*r2 + c3*r3).  That\u0027ll be hard/impossible to see in a benchmark though.",
